# Deployment Standards

## Monorepo layout

- **`frontend/`** → **Vercel** (set Git integration **Root Directory** to `frontend`, or run CLI from `frontend/`)
- **`backend/`** → **Railway**, **Render**, or **Fly.io** (recommended for ASGI) — separate project from Vercel
- Root `.env.example` documents variables for both packages

## Pre-deploy checklist

- [ ] `frontend`: `npm run build` passes
- [ ] `backend`: app starts with production env (`uvicorn` or platform start command)
- [ ] `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` = public FastAPI base URL (no trailing slash)
- [ ] `CORS_ORIGINS` includes Vercel production URL(s)
- [ ] Supabase Auth: Site URL + redirect URLs include Vercel domain
- [ ] Secrets only in host dashboards / `.env` (never committed)

## Environment variables

- `frontend/.env.local` — `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`, local dev
- `backend/.env` — `SUPABASE_*`, `CORS_ORIGINS`, secrets
- Commit **root** `.env.example` only; real values gitignored

## Vercel (Next.js)

```bash
cd frontend
npm i -g vercel
vercel login
vercel link
vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL
vercel --prod --yes
```

## Backend host (example: Railway)

Use the platform’s UI or CLI; set `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` or JWT verify vars, `CORS_ORIGINS`, and start command e.g. `uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`.

## CORS

FastAPI must allow the browser origin (`http://localhost:3000` and `https://*.vercel.app` or custom domain).
